children.subject: (Side note - according to Professor Elad, EE140 is a prereq for EE142 in case you weren't familiar with the requirements)

history.content:
142 is probably (by a good margin) the highest workload out of the three of those.  It's an outstanding class and you will learn a lot, but it is definitely something you should expect to invest significant time in to if you take it.  As Rachel mentioned below, you should also definitely plan to have 140 under your belt before taking 142.

143 and 106A are both great classes as well - I think 143 is probably higher time commitment than 106A, but the two classes are also pretty different (143 is much more lab oriented).

children.subject: Thank you for your feedback, professor!
